      "widgets_values": [
        "BIREFNET_TOONOUT\n────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n \nPurpose:\n  Anime, manga, cartoon, and digital art character extraction\n \nTraining Data:\n  - Stylized art datasets (anime, cartoon illustrations)\n  - Digital art character databases\n  - Optimized for non-photorealistic images\n \nUse Cases:\n  ✓ Anime character cutout\n  ✓ Manga panel extraction\n  ✓ Digital illustration separation\n  ✓ Cartoon character masking\n  ✓ Comic book art processing\n  ✓ Styled/filtered images\n \nPerformance Metrics:\n  - Smeasure: High on stylized content\n  - maxFm: Excellent on line art edges\n  - Focus: Sharp edges, bold outlines, solid colors\n \nStrengths:\n  ✓ Crisp edge detection on drawn characters\n  ✓ Handles bold outlines naturally\n  ✓ Works well with solid color backgrounds\n  ✓ Understands stylized proportions\n  ✓ Good on varying art styles/filters\n \nWeaknesses:\n  ✗ May over-sharpen photorealistic images\n  ✗ Less precise on soft hair (vs portrait mode)\n  ✗ Struggles with photorealistic backgrounds\n  ✗ Not ideal for grayscale/colored pencil art\n \nFile Size:\n  885 MB (safetensors)\n \nVRAM:\n  ~3.45 GB (same as General at 1024x1024)\n \nResolution Trained:\n  Standard resolution (training details not specified)\n  Works well: 512-2048px\n \nSpeed (RTX4090):\n  ~17 FPS at 1024x1024\n \nBest For:\n  - Content creators using anime/manga\n  - Game asset extraction\n  - Illustration processing\n  - Comic book digitization\n  - Stylized digital art workflows\n \nWorst Case:\n  - Photorealistic portraits (use Portrait model)\n  - Mixed photo+illustration (use General-Dynamic)\n  - Soft/blended edges (use Matting)\n \n \nBIREFNET-HR-MATTING\n────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n \nPurpose:\n  High-resolution professional image matting (alpha channel extraction)\n \nRelease Date:\n  February 12, 2025 (newest in matting line)\n \nTraining Data:\n  - P3M-10k (professional matting dataset)\n  - TR-humans (training humans set)\n  - AM-2k (additional matting data)\n  - AIM-500 (aesthetic image matting)\n  - Other professional matting datasets\n \nUse Cases:\n  ✓ Professional image compositing\n  ✓ Portrait background removal (professional)\n  ✓ Product photography editing\n  ✓ Complex soft-edge extraction\n  ✓ Hair and fur matting (precise)\n  ✓ Translucent object handling\n  ✓ Professional photo editing workflow\n \nPerformance Metrics (on TE-P3M-500-NP validation):\n  - Smeasure: 0.979 (excellent)\n  - maxFm: 0.996 (near-perfect precision)\n  - meanEm: 0.988 (exceptional accuracy)\n  - MAE: Very low (excellent alpha blending)\n \nStrengths:\n  ✓ Exceptional soft-edge handling\n  ✓ Professional-grade alpha channels\n  ✓ Handles semi-transparent objects (glass, smoke)\n  ✓ Hair matting superior to general models\n  ✓ Optimized for 2K resolution (2048x2048)\n  ✓ Trimap-free (no manual mask needed)\n  ✓ State-of-the-art performance\n  ✓ Perfect for composite work\n \nWeaknesses:\n  ✗ Slower than lightweight models\n  ✗ Higher VRAM requirement\n  ✗ Trained for fixed 2048x2048 (not dynamic)\n  ✗ Not optimized for anime/cartoon\n  ✗ Overkill for simple solid backgrounds\n \nFile Size:\n  ~450-500 MB estimated\n \nVRAM:\n  ~3.45 GB (at 2048x2048 native resolution)\n \nResolution Trained:\n  2048x2048 native (high-resolution specialist)\n \nSpeed (RTX4090):\n  ~17 FPS at native 2048x2048\n  Works at any resolution but optimized for 2K\n \nBest For:\n  - Professional photography editing\n  - Commercial compositing\n  - Precise hair/fur extraction\n  - Glass and translucent objects\n  - Fashion photography\n  - Product photography\n  - High-end post-production\n  - Creating professional overlays\n \nWorst Case:\n  - Simple flat backgrounds (overkill, use General-Lite)\n  - Real-time processing (too heavy)\n  - Anime/cartoon content (use Toonout)\n  - Variable resolution batches (use General-Dynamic)\n \n \nHEAD-TO-HEAD COMPARISON TABLE\n================================================================================\n \nFeature                TOONOUT          HR-MATTING\n────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nBest Content Type      Anime/Cartoon    Photos/Professional\nEdge Type Handling     Sharp/Bold       Soft/Blended\nHair Quality          Good              EXCELLENT\nBackground Removal    Good              Excellent\nAlpha Precision       Good              PROFESSIONAL\nSoft Edges            Poor              EXCELLENT\nTranslucent Objects   Basic             EXPERT\nTraining Data         Art               Professional\nResolution Optimized  Standard          2048x2048\nVRAM Usage            Standard          Standard\nFile Size             885MB             ~450MB\nSpeed                 17 FPS            17 FPS\nMatting Quality       Good              SOTA\nRealistic Photos      Fair              EXCELLENT\nIllustration Quality  EXCELLENT         Fair\nMixed Content         Fair              Good\n \nVerdict:\n────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nChoose TOONOUT if:\n  - Processing anime, manga, cartoons exclusively\n  - Want crisp line-art results\n  - Working with digital illustration\n \nChoose HR-MATTING if:\n  - Need professional-grade output\n  - Working with photographs\n  - Doing professional compositing\n  - Hair/soft-edge precision matters\n  - Using at 2K+ resolution\n  - Need alpha channel quality\n \n \nWORKFLOW INTEGRATION EXAMPLE (COMFYUI)\n================================================================================\n \nANIME WORKFLOW:\n  Input Image → BiRefNet_toonout → Show Text (preview)\n  Output → Super Saver (PNG alpha)\n \nPROFESSIONAL PHOTO WORKFLOW:\n  Input Image → BiRefNet_HR-matting → Crop/Scale (if >2K)\n  Output → Super Saver (PNG alpha + metadata)\n \nHYBRID WORKFLOW:\n  Input → Check Content Type → Route:\n    - Has anime: Use Toonout branch\n    - Photo: Use HR-Matting branch\n    - Output to respective pipelines\n \n \nSTORAGE RECOMMENDATION\n================================================================================\n \nIf VRAM/Disk Limited (pick ONE):\n  → BiRefNet_toonout (885MB) = Anime focus\n \nIf Balanced Setup (pick TWO):\n  → BiRefNet_toonout + BiRefNet-HR-matting\n  → Total disk: ~1.3 GB\n  → Switch between based on content\n \nIf Professional Only:\n  → BiRefNet_HR-matting + General-Dynamic\n  → Better for mixed workflows\n \n \nCOMMON USE CASES\n================================================================================\n \nTOONOUT Examples:\n  ✓ Extract anime character from fanart\n  ✓ Process manga panels for digitization\n  ✓ Remove background from cartoon\n  ✓ Stylized game asset creation\n  ✓ Digital illustration cleanup\n  ✓ Comic book page extraction\n \nHR-MATTING Examples:\n  ✓ Professional portrait background removal\n  ✓ Create product photo cutouts\n  ✓ Extract actor from movie still\n  ✓ Glass/water object matting\n  ✓ Hair-over-shoulder compositing\n  ✓ Fashion photography editing\n  ✓ Stock photo preparation\n \n \nSOURCES\n================================================================================\n \nOfficial GitHub: https://github.com/ZhengPeng7/BiRefNet\nOfficial Paper: Bilateral Reference for High-Resolution Dichotomous Image Segmentation\nPublished: CAAI AIR 2024\n \nComfyUI Integration: https://github.com/lldacing/ComfyUI_BiRefNet_ll\n \nHuggingFace Models: https://huggingface.co/ZhengPeng7/\n \nBiRefNet Toonout: https://huggingface.co/1038lab/BiRefNet\nBiRefNet HR-Matting: https://huggingface.co/ZhengPeng7/BiRefNet_HR-matting\n \nCurrent Version: February 2025 (HR-Matting latest, Toonout community)\n"
